OL,4,Cand stealing more than #3,000 cash
OL,6,F"This was a carefully orchestrated
OL,7,Fincident, and Vaughan went to great
OL,8,Flengths to plan and co-ordinate the
OL,9,Fburglary.
OL,11,F"During the incident, not only did he
OL,12,Fsteal more than #3,000 cash, but he
OL,13,Falso caused more than #35,000 worth of
OL,14,Fdamage to the store, which led to the
OL,15,Fstore being closed for two days,
OL,16,Fresulting in the loss of #24,000 trade.
